Given an integer array nums, return the third distinct maximum number in this array. If the third maximum does not exist, return the maximum number.

Solution

 class Solution {
    public int thirdMax(int[] nums) {

        Integer largest = null;
        Integer slargest = null;
        Integer tlargest = null;

        for (int num : nums) {

            // FIX: null check before comparison
            if ((largest != null && num == largest) ||
                (slargest != null && num == slargest) ||
                (tlargest != null && num == tlargest)) {
                continue;
            }

            if (largest == null || num > largest) {
                tlargest = slargest;
                slargest = largest;
                largest = num;
            } 
            else if (slargest == null || num > slargest) {
                tlargest = slargest;
                slargest = num;
            } 
            else if (tlargest == null || num > tlargest) {
                tlargest = num;
            }
        }

        return (tlargest == null) ? largest : tlargest;
    }
}
